                            <comment id="15428360" author="garydgregory" created="Fri, 19 Aug 2016 15:58:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi All:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Should the option name be &lt;tt&gt;lazyCreate&lt;/tt&gt; or &lt;tt&gt;createOnDemand&lt;/tt&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have &lt;tt&gt;lazyCreate&lt;/tt&gt; in there now but when wrote the docs for the site just now (I had forgotten) the term &quot;on-demand&quot; sounds better and feels more accessible.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thoughts?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Gary&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15428370" author="remkop@yahoo.com" created="Fri, 19 Aug 2016 16:09:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I also think &quot;create on demand&quot; is more descriptive. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15429591" author="garydgregory" created="Sun, 21 Aug 2016 05:27:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In Git master.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15535454" author="remkop@yahoo.com" created="Fri, 30 Sep 2016 08:52:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=garydgregory&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;garydgregory&quot;&gt;garydgregory&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/logging-log4j2/blob/master/src/site/xdoc/manual/appenders.xml#L2211&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Appenders documentation&lt;/a&gt;, could you mention the default value for the new &lt;tt&gt;createOnDemand&lt;/tt&gt; attribute?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
